              <h3>
               Study Abroad in Greece: Feb. 1 Deadline
              </h3>
              <i aria-hidden="true" class="fa fa-calendar">
              </i>
              <span class="date-display-single">
               January 15, 2019
              </span>
              <br/>
              <p>
               <span>
                The department is offering a new study abroad opportunity,
                <span>
                </span>
               </span>
               <strong>
                PHIL 3390/5050: What is the Life Worth Living? Ancient Ethics in Athens
               </strong>
               <span>
                , which goes to Greece for eight days in the summer semester (May 12-21, 2019). The bulk of the course takes place in Athens, with day trips to the mountains of Delphi and the Greek Island of Hydra, where you and...
               </span>
              </p>
              <p>
               <a alt=" Study Abroad in Greece: Feb. 1 Deadline" class="button button-green" href="/study-abroad-greece-feb-1-deadline" title=" Study Abroad in Greece: Feb. 1 Deadline">
